Antonius getting the upper hand, Cic. retires from Rome and betakes himself to his country houses, where he writes the de natura deorum, the essays de divinatione, de fato, de amicitia, de senec- tute, de gloria, and commences the de officiis. He then projects a journey to Greece but returns after getting as far as Sicily, and reaches Rome Aug. 31. On Sept. 2 he delivers the first Plzilzjopze, and soon after writes the second, and on Dec. 18, when Antony had left Rome because of the defec- tion of the fourth and Martian legions, delivers the third and fourth Philippics.
